1ï¸âƒ£ Anagram Check
ğŸ”¹ Problem

Check if two strings are anagrams
(They contain the same characters with the same frequency)

ğŸ§  Python Code (2 lines)
s1="listen"; s2="silent"
print(sorted(s1)==sorted(s2))

ğŸ“– Explanation

sorted(s1) sorts characters of the first string.

sorted(s2) sorts characters of the second string.

If both sorted lists are equal â†’ strings are anagrams.

ğŸ§  Simple Example (Think Like This)

"listen" â†’ ['e','i','l','n','s','t']

"silent" â†’ ['e','i','l','n','s','t']

Same characters â†’ Anagram

â±ï¸ Interview Insight

Time Complexity: O(n log n)

Space Complexity: O(n)

ğŸ¤ Interview Explanation

â€œI sort both strings and compare them. If they match, the strings are anagrams.â€

2ï¸âƒ£ Substring Basics
ğŸ”¹ Problem

Print all substrings of a string.

ğŸ§  Python Code (4 lines)
s="abc"
for i in range(len(s)):
    for j in range(i+1,len(s)+1):
        print(s[i:j])

ğŸ–¥ï¸ Output
a
ab
abc
b
bc
c

ğŸ“– Explanation

A substring is a continuous part of a string.

Outer loop selects the start index.

Inner loop selects the end index.

s[i:j] extracts the substring.

â±ï¸ Interview Insight

Time Complexity: O(nÂ²)

Used in:

Sliding window

Longest substring problems

ğŸ¤ Interview Explanation

â€œI fix a starting index and expand the ending index to generate all continuous substrings.â€

ğŸ¤ FAANG Interview Round (Professional Answers)

Q1. What is an anagram?
A: Two strings that contain the same characters with the same frequency.

Q2. Difference between substring and subsequence?
A: Substring is continuous; subsequence may skip characters.

Q3. Can anagram be solved without sorting?
A: Yes, using hashing (frequency count).

Q4. Where are substrings used?
A: Sliding window, pattern matching, longest substring problems.
